observations.recommendation:
a. The GSO update the property cards (PCs) to include all acquisitions, issues, and disposal of PPE, if any;
b. the GSO prepares the list of PPEs found at the station and submits it to the Accounting Unit for recording in the books;
c. The GSO makes a list of missing/non-existing PPEs, observes the guidelines for the disposition of said properties, and completes all the procedures prescribed in the one-time cleansing of PPE account balances enumerated under Item 6.3.1 (a to h) of COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020;
d. The Accounting Unit takes up accounting entries to recognize PPE found at the station prepares and maintains corresponding PPELCs based on the list submitted by the GSO and adheres to all the procedures stated in Item 6.3.2 (a to f) of COA Circular No. 2020-006 dated January 31, 2020;
e. Ensure that Property Acknowledgement Receipts (PARs) are strictly prepared for all acquired or procured properties. PARs are to be utilized for documenting the receipt of property and equipment intended for official use from the Designated Property Officer; and
f. The GSO and Accounting Unit reconcile their records and ensure that the Property Cards (PCs) maintained by the Property Unit and the PPE ledger cards (PPELCs) maintained by the Accounting Unit are reconciled.

a. The City Accountant reclassify the issued tangible items prior to CY 2022 with carrying below the ₱50,000.00 threshold and expense the same to Prior Period Adjustment and Government Equity, while tangible items that are still in the custody of the Supply/Property Division shall be recorded to the appropriate semi-expendable property accounts;
b. Likewise, the Accountant adjust the opening balance in the Statement of Changes in Net Assets/Equity in compliance with COA Circular No. 2022-004, dated May 31, 2022; and
c. The GSO maintain the Semi-expendable Property Cards (SPCs) for semi-expendable items under custody until these items are issued to end-users.

a. Submit all cash advance vouchers for CF with the required supporting document, within seven working days from the release of the check to the COA Audit Team Leader (ATL)/Regional Supervising Auditor (RSA)/Supervising Auditor (SA) concerned in a sealed envelope with a visible label “CONFIDENTIAL – For the COA ATL Only” and with a covering transmittal letter enumerating the submissions pursuant to Item 6.3.3.d COA, DILG, Governance Commission for GOCCs, and DND Joint Circular No. 2015-01 dated January 8, 2015;
b. Ensure that supporting documents for the grant of cash advance are complete and sufficient and in accordance with the itemized documents under Item 6.1.7 and Item 6.1.8.3 of said Joint Circular; and
c. Secure a certification from the concerned PNP Chief relative to the peace and order situation in the locality highlighting in concrete detail the circumstances that require the urgency of allocating the CF and supporting the need to release and use the CF.

1) The GSO to follow the procedures prescribed in the one-time cleansing of PPE account balances and ensure the updating of the Property Cards by posting all unrecorded acquisition/receipt, issue/transfer, and disposal of PPE;
2) The GSO to prepare the list of PPEs found at the station and provide property cards, make a list of missing/non-existent PPEs, and observe the procedures for the disposition of said properties;
3) The Accounting Unit to take up accounting entries to recognize PPE found at the station and its losses, set up the corresponding receivables from the concerned accountable officer/personnel, update the PPELC/SL, and ensure the total balance of PPELCs/SLs tally with the balances of controlling PPE accounts in the General Ledger; and
4) The GSO and Accounting units to reconcile their records in accordance with COA Circular No. 2020-006.

We recommended that the City Government submit the following documents:
a) Copy of the composition of the PRAISE Committee;
b) Copy of the City’s CSC-Approved PRAISE;
c) Performance Ratings of each permanent officers and employees;
d) Basis for the amount given;
e) Criteria in granting the PRAISE Bonus as recommended by the City PRAISE Committee;
f) List of Savings and Monetary Awards earned / generated during CY 2015 and relevant supporting documents;
g) Evaluation reports or any documentation recognizing the productivity, creativeness, innovation made/or ethical behavior of employees or group of employees making them eligible for the PRAISE; and
h) Specific legal basis which allows the grant of the incentives in the absence of the above requirements, otherwise the incentives granted be refunded immediately.

