We recommended that the City Government:

Implement strictly the provisions of RA 9003 and intensify the “no segregation, no collection policy” among residents of every barangay.  Further, direct all barangay and barangay officials to coordinate closely with the Solid Waste               Management Board (SWMB) on this policy;

Implement the closure of the open dump site as mandated     under Section 41 of RA 9003 and the possibility of            converting the present dump site into a sanitary landfill and/or converting a new technological approach to solid waste management where wastes are better managed,      controlled and contained;

Engage additional dump trucks to haul solid wastes of all      barangays and provide specific collection schedules for each type of waste;

Direct the SWMB to ensure that all barangays in the City      establish Material Recovery Facilities pursuant to Section 32 of RA 9003; and

Exercise strong political will to implement the                     environmental laws on preserving and protecting the        environment as mandated by the Act.

